race.comment: STARTLING STAR (2) closed off strongly from well back under the apprentice to be 3.2L off the winner over 1800m last time out as favourite. She now rises in trip again and gets CJP in the saddle this time from a better gate. Expecting her to sit closer this time and with her upside, she looks very hard to beat. DANDY'S GEM (5) led them up last start at Ascot and was only collared late, beaten 0.4L. Expect her to take up the running once again from an inside barrier for Ramoly. A slight gear change will help and she'll be tough to run down. ZOOMACHINO (3) ran over the top to score at Northam last time out, winning by 0.4L over 2212m. Chris Parnham sticks with her following her maiden win and she can improve further with that added confidence. AL UNIQUE (1) is racing well without winning and should get his chance from an inside barrier. HIGH PRECISION (7) is better suited back out in trip today and ticks plenty of boxes.
